description: Alassana Jatta scored twice as Notts County won a thrilling League Two contest at Cheltenham 5-3
title: Alassana Jatta scored twice as Notts County won a thrilling League Two contest at Cheltenham 5-3
title_page: Alassana Jatta scored twice as Notts County won a thrilling League Two contest at Cheltenham 5-3 - BBC Sport
maintext:
Cheltenham Town won both of their Football League games when they last met Notts County during the 2018-19 season, winning this exact fixture 4-1.
Notts County have won just one of their last five away Football League games against Cheltenham Town (D2 L2), with both sides scoring in each of the last four such games.
Cheltenham have won their final Football League game of a calendar year on just one of the last 10 occasions (D5 L4), though are unbeaten in the last two (W1 D1).
Notts County are looking to win their final Football League game of a year in successive years for the first time since 1991 (run of four), after beating Morecambe 5-0 last year.
